g.title: Layer 1
g.text: Long-term Heart Risk Prediction by Survival Analysis in Echocardiography
Leveraging Machine Learning, Interpretability Techniques, and Advanced Statistical Modelling
Age, WMI, FS, PE, WMS, etc.
1. From Linear to Non-linear Hazard Modeling
X·β = sum(m=1 to M) βm X^pm
h_FPM(t|X) = h0(t) · exp(sum(m=1 to M) βm X^pm)
2. From Black-box Prediction to Interpretable Models
3. From Static to Dynamic Risk Evolution
H_RSF(t) = -log S(t) = sum(i=1 to n) di/ni
WMI: Wall Motion Index, FS: Fractional Shortening, PE: Pericardial Effusion, WMS: Wall Motion Score, FP: Fractional Polynomial, RSF: Random Survival Forest
